        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-02-14T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-02-14T17:00:00-05:00" n="84" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d84">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851G.00/2–1047: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Consulate</gloss> at Hanoi</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-02-14T17:00:00-05:00">February 14, 1947—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>15. <gloss target="#t_urtel1">Urtel</gloss> 51 Feb. 10.<note n="55" xml:id="d84fn55">Not printed.</note> Re Vietnam report that Secy’s
                    declaration showed that international opinion does not wish see war in Vietnam,
                    Secy in Feb 7 press conf said for attribution but not quotation “We are
                    naturally deeply interested troubled situation Indochina and naturally are
                    hopeful they can find pacific basis for its adjustment”.</p>
                <p>Sent Hanoi 15. Repeated Saigon 32.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
